    Use a multicast socket to listen for probe requests  
   
   
    diag.enable_tcp  
    Use a TCP socket to listen for probe requests (ignored if  enable_diagnostics  is false)  
   
   
    diag.mcast_addr  
    The multicast address which the MulticastSocket should join. The default is
                     224.0.75.75  for IPv4 and  ff0e::0:75:75  for IPv6.  
   
   
    diag.bind_addr  
    Bind address for diagnostic probing. Used when diag_enable_tcp is true")  
   
   
    diag.port  
    The port on which the MulticastSocket should listen. The default is  7500 .  
   
   
   
   
   Probe is extensible; by implementing a ProbeHandler and registering it with the
              transport (TP.registerProbeHandler()), any protocol, or even
               applications  can register functionality to be invoked via probe. Refer to the
