 It’s prudent to advise setting up local network and logging properties while noting risks related to optional subsystems needing external dependencies. I need to ensure the JSON format is valid too.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"JGroups has no required runtime dependencies or external services, but generated tests should force local loopback networking and stable JDK logging to avoid multicast/interface/logging variability in JVM and native runs.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Set system properties for both JVM tests and native-test runtime: jgroups.bind_addr=127.0.0.1, java.net.preferIPv4Stack=true, and jgroups.use.jdk_logger=true. Prefer in-process stacks such as SHARED_LOOPBACK with SHARED_LOOPBACK_PING for channel/message/view coverage. Avoid default UDP multicast discovery and external JDBC services; JDBC_PING can be covered with a fake java.sql.Driver or no-op driver class.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Default JGroups UDP/multicast stacks can be flaky or unavailable in CI/native-image environments.\",\n    \"Optional logging and OpenSSL code paths are classpath-sensitive; do not add SLF4J, Log4j2, or WildFly OpenSSL unless the generated tests intentionally exercise those optional integrations.\",\n    \"JDBC_PING and cloud/discovery protocols can imply external infrastructure if tested naively; use local stubs instead.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0dbd81b02349aae3016a4272447bec8190a2509a5f59348d88\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 991, "output": 1675, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31338, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782739501412, "responseId": "resp_0dbd81b02349aae3016a42722de4108190aa6e9b0821b7fd56"}}
